Vol / Page: 56
Edition:
Quote: The name `cod' is applied to many fishes, often quite unrelated. True cods (family Gadidae), typified by the common Northern Hemisphere cod, are represented in New Zealand by only two species. The so-called `cods' of our waters belong to other families.
